HEADWORD: Recouch
<hw>Re*couch"</hw> <pr>(r?*kouch")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>re-</ets> + <ets>couch</ets>: cf. F. <ets>recoucher</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To retire again to a couch; to lie down again.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

